{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T11:05:45.516Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Teacher Forcing Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":" is a training technique used in sequence-to-sequence (Seq2Seq) models where, at each decoding step, the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"correct target token from the training data (ground truth)"},{"type":"text","text":" is fed as input to the next step instead of the model's own prediction. It's like a teacher correcting a student after each wrong answer so they can learn the correct sequence faster."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Teacher Forcing Matters in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Teacher forcing is crucial for training Seq2Seq models because it:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Impact"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Faster learning"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model learns sequences more quickly"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stable training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prevents error accumulation and drifting into bad predictions"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Better convergence"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Avoids going off-track early in training"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Accelerated training time"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reduces training time significantly"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without teacher forcing, if the model predicts the wrong word at step 1, it uses that wrong prediction for step 2, leading to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"compounding errors"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Teacher Forcing Works (Mechanics)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Normal Decoding (Without Teacher Forcing):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"At each time step t:\n  Input: Previous prediction (model's own output) + Hidden state\n  Output: Next token prediction\n  \nExample: Target = \"I am learning\"\n  Step 1: Predict \"I\" ✅\n  Step 2: Uses \"I\" → Predicts \"Is\" ❌\n  Step 3: Uses \"is\" → Everything goes off track ❌❌❌\n  \nProblem: One mistake compounds into many mistakes"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"With Teacher Forcing:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"At each time step t:\n  Input: Ground truth token (from training data) + Hidden state\n  Output: Next token prediction\n  \nExample: Target = \"I am learning\"\n  Step 1: Uses ground truth \"I\" → Predicts \"I\" (correct)\n  Step 2: Uses ground truth \"am\" → Predicts \"am\" (correct)\n  Step 3: Uses ground truth \"learning\" → Predicts \"learning\" (correct)\n  \nBenefit: Even if model makes mistake, we replace with correct token"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key concept"},{"type":"text","text":": The decoder gets the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"true previous output"},{"type":"text","text":" as input, not the model's prediction."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Teacher Forcing Process"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Training Data:\n  Input: [\"hello\"] (English)\n  Target: [\"bonjour\"] (French)\n\nDecoder Input with Teacher Forcing:\n  Step 1: <BOS> (start token) + encoder output → Predict \"bonjour\"\n  Step 2: \"bonjour\" (ground truth) + encoder output → Predict \"end\"\n  Step 3: \"end\" (ground truth) → Stop\n\nNote: We feed the ground truth tokens [\"bonjour\", \"end\"] as input,\nnot the model's predictions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The process of concatenating "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<BOS>"},{"type":"text","text":" and the original output sequence (excluding the final token) as input to the decoder during training is called "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Problem: Exposure Bias (Train-Test Gap)"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Training"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inference (Test)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Input"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ground truth tokens"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model's own predictions"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Error handling"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistakes corrected immediately"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistakes compound"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Availability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Have ground truth"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No ground truth"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The problem"},{"type":"text","text":": If you always use teacher forcing, the model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"never learns to recover from its own mistakes"},{"type":"text","text":" because at test time, it won't have ground truth inputs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This mismatch is called "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exposure bias"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"During training"},{"type":"text","text":": Model always sees correct context\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"During inference"},{"type":"text","text":": Model must use its own (possibly wrong) predictions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":": Errors can accumulate at inference since the model has never learned to recover from its own mistakes."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Solution: Scheduled Sampling"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scheduled sampling"},{"type":"text","text":" is a technique that mixes teacher forcing with free running (using predictions):"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Strategy"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Teacher Forcing"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Always feeds ground-truth tokens → fast training, but exposure bias"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scheduled Sampling"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mixes ground-truth and predicted tokens according to a schedule"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Implementation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gradually reduce teacher forcing rate from 100% → 0% as model improves"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reduces train-test mismatch and improves robustness"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Early training (model is weak):\n  90% teacher forcing (use ground truth)\n  10% free running (use predictions)\n  \nLater training (model improves):\n  50% teacher forcing\n  50% free running\n  \nEnd training (model expert):\n  0% teacher forcing\n  100% free running"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This allows the model to learn to recover from mistakes while still benefiting from stable early training."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Machine Translation with Teacher Forcing"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Input: [\"I\", \"love\", \"AI\"] (English)\nTarget: [\"J'aime\", \"l'\", \"IA\"] (French)\n\nWithout Teacher Forcing:\n  Step 1: Input <BOS> → Predict \"J'aime\" ✅\n  Step 2: Input \"J'aime\" (model's prediction) → Predict \"le\" ❌\n  Step 3: Input \"le\" (wrong prediction) → Predict \"chat\" ❌❌\n  \nResult: \"J'aime le chat\" (WRONG)\n\nWith Teacher Forcing:\n  Step 1: Input <BOS> → Predict \"J'aime\" (correct)\n  Step 2: Input \"J'aime\" (ground truth) → Predict \"l'\" (correct)\n  Step 3: Input \"l'\" (ground truth) → Predict \"IA\" (correct)\n  \nResult: \"J'aime l'IA\" (CORRECT)\n\nNote: Even if model predicts wrong at step 2, we feed ground truth \"l'\" \nfor step 3"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits of Teacher Forcing"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explanation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stable gradients"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model always conditions on correct context"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Faster convergence"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Learning is accelerated"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prevents error compounding"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"One mistake doesn't ruin the entire sequence"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Better early training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Essential when model is trying to converge"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs & Limitations"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Limitation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explanation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exposure bias"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Train-test mismatch (model never learns to recover from mistakes)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Over-reliance"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model becomes dependent on ground truth inputs"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No error recovery"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can't learn to fix its own mistakes during inference"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Inference gap"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Teacher forcing not available during production/testing"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Solutions"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scheduled sampling"},{"type":"text","text":": Gradually reduce teacher forcing\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Attention forcing"},{"type":"text","text":": Guide model with generated output + reference attention"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of teacher forcing as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"student learning to spell"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":": Student writes \"cat\" → guesses \"c-a-t\" ✅, then \"dog\" → guesses \"d-o-c\" ❌, then uses \"d-o-c\" to guess \"cat\" → gets \"c-a-c\" ❌❌"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":": Student writes \"cat\" → guesses \"c-a-t\" ✅, teacher corrects to \"c-a-t\" (if wrong), then writes \"dog\" → guesses \"d-o-g\" ✅"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The teacher immediately supplies the correct word so the student can use it for the next prediction"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Or think of it as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"learning a dance"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":": You practice alone, make mistakes, and those mistakes become your new \"normal\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":": Instructor corrects your move immediately, so you learn the right sequence"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":" feeds the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ground truth token"},{"type":"text","text":" (correct target from training data) as input to the next decoding step instead of the model's own prediction"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Purpose"},{"type":"text","text":": Accelerates learning, stabilizes training, and prevents error accumulation"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":": Mistakes compound → one wrong prediction ruins the entire sequence"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With teacher forcing"},{"type":"text","text":": Even if model makes a mistake, we replace it with the correct token before moving forward"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exposure bias"},{"type":"text","text":": The main problem — model never learns to recover from mistakes because ground truth isn't available at inference"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scheduled sampling"},{"type":"text","text":": The solution — gradually reduce teacher forcing rate during training so model learns to use its own predictions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Essential for"},{"type":"text","text":": Machine translation, text summarization, speech recognition, chatbots"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Industry standard"},{"type":"text","text":": Used in most Seq2Seq models (RNNs, LSTMs, GRUs, Transformers) with encoder-decoder architectures"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Teacher forcing is a critical training technique that enables Seq2Seq models to learn sequences efficiently, but it must be balanced with exposure bias mitigation strategies like scheduled sampling for robust inference."}]}]}}
